[This article seems to have some contradictions. The article states:

1) The test results mark the 5th incident of CWD discovered in Montana wild deer this fall [2017], but the 1st in northern Montana.

2) Until this year [2017], CWD had not been found in Montana, though the disease exists in wild deer herds in Wyoming, North and South Dakota, Saskatchewan and Alberta.

Clearly, if this is the 5th case in Montana, then it is not the 1st in the state, but it may be the 1st in a particular region of the state, in which case, this represents an expansion of the disease in the state of Montana. - Mod.TG

